File: internal/domain/security/material.go
Package: security
Purpose: Defines fixed-size byte array value objects for cryptographic materials isolation.
Constants: DerivationSignatureSize=64, KEKSize=32, SaltSize=32, DeviceIDSize=16.
Types: DerivationSignature [64]byte, AccountUnlockKey [32]byte, DeviceKEK [32]byte, AccountSalt [32]byte, DeviceID [16]byte.
Functions:
func NewDerivationSignature(raw []byte) (DerivationSignature, error). Purpose: validates len==64, returns copy. Errors: invalid derivation signature length on length mismatch.
Zero Value: Zeroed materials are invalid for operational use.

File: internal/domain/security/kek.go
Package: security
Purpose: Implements two-step domain-separated KEK derivation using HKDF-SHA256.
Constants: infoAccountUnlockKey=gophkeeper-account-unlock-v1, infoDeviceKEK=gophkeeper-device-kek-v1.
Functions:
func DeriveAccountUnlockKey(signature DerivationSignature, accountSalt AccountSalt) (AccountUnlockKey, error). Purpose: derives root account key via HKDF-SHA256 with signature as IKM and accountSalt as salt. Errors: derive account unlock key on reader failures.
func DeriveDeviceKEK(accountUnlockKey AccountUnlockKey, deviceID DeviceID) (DeviceKEK, error). Purpose: derives container-specific key via HKDF-SHA256 with accountUnlockKey as IKM and deviceID as salt. Errors: derive device kek on reader failures.
Security Constraints: Strict domain separation via fixed info labels ensures key isolation. io.ReadFull guarantees exactly 32 bytes extraction.

File: internal/domain/security/derivation_payload.go
Package: security
Purpose: Constructs and serializes deterministic derivation payload for local account unlocking.
Constants: DerivationPayloadVersion=1, DerivationPayloadContext=gophkeeper-account-unlock-v1, maxEncodedFieldLen=65535.
Globals and Init: ErrEmptyUserID, ErrInvalidUserID, ErrEmptySSHFingerprint, ErrEncodedFieldTooLong, ErrInvalidDerivationVersion: domain validation targets.
Types: DerivationPayload struct. Holds Version uint32, Context string, UserID [16]byte, SSHFingerprint []byte.
Functions:
func NewDerivationPayload(userID string, sshFingerprint []byte) (DerivationPayload, error). Purpose: builder validation. Errors: ErrEmptyUserID; ErrInvalidUserID on bad UUID; ErrEmptySSHFingerprint.
func MarshalDerivationPayload(userID string, sshFingerprint []byte) ([]byte, error). Convenience encoder.
func (p DerivationPayload) MarshalBinary() ([]byte, error). Purpose: encodes schema to BigEndian structure with uint16 length prefixes. Errors: ErrInvalidDerivationVersion; ErrEmptyUserID; ErrEmptySSHFingerprint; field encoding failures.
func writeBinaryBytes(buf *bytes.Buffer, data []byte) error. Internal BigEndian uint16 length-prefixed writer. Errors: ErrEncodedFieldTooLong.
Security Constraints: Strict binary layout enforces exact matching with server-side validation schemes.
